---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const pageContent = "<section class=\"mc-about\">\n\n  <h1>About Mitch Chadban</h1>\n\n  <h2>\nDesigner and marketer focused on one thing: work that looks great and gets results. I build brand systems, design assets, and marketing that turns attention into action.\n  </h2>\n\n  <div class=\"img-full-ctm\">\n    <img class=\"\" src=\"/images/C2.png\" alt=\"Plexiglass Chadban logo with moss and mushrooms growing on it\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2784\" height=\"1126\">\n  </div>\n\n  <h3>What I do (in plain English)</h3>\n  <p>\nI help businesses look credible and consistent, then turn that into momentum. That means building brand systems (logo, templates, collateral, content) and supporting the marketing side — messaging, funnels, SEO/AEO, and campaigns — so the work doesn’t just look good, it pulls leads.\n  </p>\n\n  <h3>What I’m known for</h3>\n  <p>\nStrong, character-led illustration is still part of the toolkit — but the bigger thing people hire me for now is clarity + consistency: visuals that feel distinct, a message that lands, and assets that actually ship (social, ads, landing pages, decks, one-pagers).\n  </p>\n\n  <p>\nI’m equally comfortable designing for culture (music, events, hospitality) and for growth (SaaS, services, online brands) — especially when a brand needs to stop looking generic and start converting attention into enquiries.\n  </p>\n\n  <h3>How I work</h3>\n  <p>\nI work like a designer who’s been forced to care about results (because that’s what clients actually want).\n  </p>\n\n  <ul>\n    <li>System-first: brand rules + templates so everything stays consistent</li>\n    <li>Marketing-aware: message match from ad → landing page → CTA</li>\n    <li>Fast iteration: ship, test, refine (without endless “make it pop” loops)</li>\n    <li>Digital-forward: vector-heavy, with traditional touches when they add bite</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <p class=\"mc-about__goal\">\nThe goal is always the same: distinct work that holds up in the real world — and supports what you’re trying to achieve (leads, sales, sign-ups, bookings).\n  </p>\n\n  <h3>Background</h3>\n  <p>\nGraduated from Newcastle University (Visual Communication). Since then: years across music, hospitality, and brands that want to look sharper and more memorable — now expanded into the marketing layer: positioning, messaging, funnels, and SEO/AEO for businesses that need growth, not just aesthetics.\n  </p>\n\n  <p>If you want a brand that looks legit and performs, we’ll get along.\n  </p>\n\n  <div class=\"img-full-ctm\">\n    <img class=\"zoomable\" src=\"/images/Cban-1.png\" alt=\"A metal bust statue of Mitch Chadban\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1080\" height=\"692\">\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"mc-about__note\">\n    <small>Life without vice is like meece without mice!</small>\n  </div>\n  <br />\n  <br />\n</section>";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Mitch Chadban"
  description="Meet Mitch Chadban, an Australia-based designer and marketer building brand systems, sharp visuals and SEO/AEO that turn attention into real leads and sales."
  canonical="https://mitchchadban.com/about/"
>
  <Fragment set:html={pageContent} />
</BaseLayout>
